---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const timelineEvents = [
  { year: '4 BCE', title: 'Born at Corduba', desc: 'Born in Corduba (modern Córdoba), Spain, to the rhetorician Annaeus Seneca.' },
  { year: '5 CE', title: 'Brought to Rome', desc: 'His aunt brought him to Rome as an infant, where he was educated in rhetoric and philosophy.' },
  { year: '31 CE', title: 'Entered Public Life', desc: 'Began his career at the Roman bar and won early distinction as an orator.' },
  { year: '41 CE', title: 'Exiled to Corsica', desc: 'Banished by Emperor Claudius on a charge of adultery — spent eight years in exile.' },
  { year: '49 CE', title: 'Recalled to Rome', desc: 'Agrippina recalled him to tutor her young son, the future Emperor Nero.' },
  { year: '54 CE', title: 'Advisor to Nero', desc: 'Became one of the most powerful men in the Empire, guiding Nero\'s early reign.' },
  { year: '62 CE', title: 'Retirement', desc: 'Withdrew from public life, attempting to return his wealth to Nero. Devoted himself to philosophy.' },
  { year: '63–65 CE', title: 'Wrote the Letters', desc: '124 letters to Lucilius — his most mature philosophical work, written in retirement.', highlight: true },
  { year: '65 CE', title: 'Death', desc: 'Ordered to take his own life by Nero after the Pisonian conspiracy. Died with Stoic composure.' },
];
---

<Layout title="About - Letters to Lucilius">
  <Header currentPath="/about" />

  <main class="about">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about__content">
        <h1 class="about__title">About</h1>

        <div class="about__section">
          <p class="about__lead">
            The <em>Letters to Lucilius</em> represent one of history's most profound collections of philosophical wisdom — a masterwork of Roman Stoicism that has guided readers for nearly two millennia.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about__section">
          <h2>About Seneca</h2>
          <p>
            Lucius Annaeus Seneca (4 BCE – 65 CE) was born at Corduba in Spain to the talented rhetorician Annaeus Seneca. Educated at Rome, he was soon attracted to Stoic philosophy — "the stern nurse of heroes during the first century of the Empire."
          </p>
          <p>
            His life reads like a Roman tragedy: prominent at the bar, exiled to Corsica for eight years, recalled in 49 CE to tutor the young Nero, and ultimately rising to become one of the most powerful men in the Empire. The contradictions are striking — a Stoic preaching simplicity who amassed enormous wealth. Yet his philosophical works, particularly these letters written in his final years, represent his most mature thought.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Life Timeline -->
        <div class="about__section">
          <h2>The Life of Seneca</h2>
          <div class="timeline">
            {timelineEvents.map(event => (
              <div class={`timeline__event ${event.highlight ? 'timeline__event--highlight' : ''}`}>
                <div class="timeline__year-col">
                  <span class="timeline__year">{event.year}</span>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline__line-col">
                  <span class="timeline__dot"></span>
                  <span class="timeline__line"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline__content-col">
                  <h3 class="timeline__event-title">{event.title}</h3>
                  <p class="timeline__event-desc">{event.desc}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about__section">
          <h2>About This Collection</h2>
          <p>
            This digital collection presents all 124 surviving letters from Seneca's <em>Epistulae Morales ad Lucilium</em>, written between 63–65 CE. These letters "form a collection of essays rather than letters" in the traditional sense — each beginning with a concrete incident that leads to deeper philosophical reflection.
          </p>
          <p>
            Modern readers will find themes that feel remarkably contemporary: the dignity of intellectual work, protests against slavery, advocacy for equality, appreciation for plain living, and what one scholar calls "the beauty of holiness" presented from a Roman standpoint.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about__section">
          <h2>Why Read the Letters Today?</h2>
          <p>
            Seneca writes not as an academic philosopher but as someone who navigated the complexities of wealth and power, health and illness, friendship and betrayal. The letters demonstrate philosophy's true purpose: not intellectual exercise but practical wisdom for daily life.
          </p>
          <p>
            Modern readers will find something increasingly rare: a mature mind wrestling honestly with life's fundamental questions, offering guidance tested against reality's demands.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about__section">
          <h2>About This Project</h2>
          <p>
            Hi, my name is Bhuvan. I stumbled onto Seneca's letters while browsing Wikisource and was floored by the depth of wisdom. I thought more people should read these — they're in the public domain but not easy to access. So I created this site to present them in a clean, readable format.
          </p>
          <p>
            Maybe you'll read a letter or two. Maybe you'll find some wisdom that helps you deal with the vagaries of life. That's the hope.
          </p>
          <div class="about__links">
            <a href="https://bebhuvan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">bebhuvan.com</a>
            <a href="https://www.rabbitholes.garden/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">rabbitholes.garden</a>
            <a href="https://bhuvan.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">newsletter</a>
            <a href="https://twitter.com/bebhuvan" target="_blank" rel="noopener">twitter</a>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bebhuvan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-24);
  }

  .about__content {
    max-width: var(--max-width-prose);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 8vw, 5.5rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .about__section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .about__lead {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .about__section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .about__section p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .about__section p:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about__section em {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .about__section a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .about__section a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .about__links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about__links a {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .about__links a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* ===== Life Timeline ===== */
  .timeline {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  .timeline__event {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 24px 1fr;
    gap: 0 var(--space-4);
    min-height: 64px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .timeline__year-col {
    text-align: right;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }

  .timeline__year {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .timeline__line-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    position: relative;
  }

  .timeline__dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--border-primary);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 6px;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .timeline__line {
    width: 1px;
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--border-primary);
  }

  .timeline__event:last-child .timeline__line {
    display: none;
  }

  .timeline__content-col {
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .timeline__event-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }

  .timeline__event-desc {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Highlighted event */
  .timeline__event--highlight .timeline__year {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .timeline__event--highlight .timeline__dot {
    background: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--color-accent-light);
  }

  .timeline__event--highlight .timeline__event-title {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .timeline__event--highlight .timeline__content-col {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border-primary);
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about {
      padding: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-16);
    }

    .about__section p {
      font-size: var(--text-base);
    }

    .about__lead {
      font-size: var(--text-lg);
    }

    .timeline__event {
      grid-template-columns: 64px 20px 1fr;
      gap: 0 var(--space-3);
    }

    .timeline__year {
      font-size: 0.6875rem;
    }
  }
</style>
